description: From Latin aēneus (“made of copper or bronze”).

adjectives.description: aeneous (comparative more aeneous, superlative most aeneous)

examples: Very similar to australiensis but the postmarginal vein absent, the thorax more aeneous and more deeply punctate, umbilicately punctate, the scape is metallic only at the middle portions, the ends white and the grooves on each side of the median carina of propodeum are shallower.
